Object.Field: LKM DB2 UDB to DB2 UDB (EXPORT-IMPORT)

COMPONENT NAME: LKM DB2 UDB to DB2 UDB (EXPORT-IMPORT)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a IBM DB2 UDB database to a IBM DB2 UDB database using the native EXPORT / IMPORT Commands. - This module uses EXPORT CLP Command to extract data in a temporary file. Data is then loaded in the target temporary DB2 UDB table created dynamically using the IMPORT CLP command. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the journal table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Restrictions: - Make sure that the Data Server checkbox is checked in your Topology for the DB2 UDB Technology and, for your source and target DB2 UDB Databases, specify the Database name in the Server field of the Data Server definition. To do that: 1. Edit the "IBM DB2 UDB" Technology definition in the Topology 2. Check the Naming Rules -> Using "Data Server" checkbox 3. Used Term : "Server" 4. Apply your changes 5. Edit your source and target DB2 UDB Dataserver definitons 6. In the Server field, enter the DB2 UDB Database name - The users specified in the DB2 UDB Data Servers in the Sunopsis Topology must have enough privileges to run the IMPORT (on the source server) and EXPORT (on the target server). - The DB2 UDB Command Line Processor (CLP) as well as the DB2 UDB Connect Software must be installed on the machine running the ODI Agent. CLP directory should be in the path when Agent is started. - The temporary data file format is specified by the TEMP_FILE_TYPE option. - Specify appropriate options values according to their description. - Please refer to the IBM documentation to enhance this KM.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Additional options used when creating the C$ temporary table. You may use this option if you wish to create the temporary table in a nologging mode (transaction is not written to the DB2 log files) or if you wish to specify a tablespace name. Examples: - Disable logging: NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Specify a tablespace: IN MY_TABLESPACE NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Compress Values: VALUE COMPRESSION
Temp. Directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp
Temporary Data File Type generated by the DB2 Export Command Supported values are IXF or DEL.
